# Doing the Same Thing Over and Over

Imagine you need to print "Happy Birthday" to the console 5 times. You could do this:

```javascript
console.log("Happy Birthday");
console.log("Happy Birthday");
console.log("Happy Birthday");
console.log("Happy Birthday");
console.log("Happy Birthday");
```

That works. But what if you need to print it **100 times**? Or **a million times**? You'd be typing all day!

Computers are incredibly fast at doing repetitive tasks. We just need to know how to ask.
